# Odyssey — Project Context

Odyssey is a monorepo for **affiliate-marketing / lead-generating travel platforms**. Revenue
comes from **TradeTracker** affiliate links plus display ads. The first app (`albanie`) is a
Dutch-language travel guide for Albania, backed by the `@albanie_reizen` Instagram audience.
The platform is **multi-market by design** — successful patterns are reused for more countries.

Read `AGENTS.md` and `docs/` for full context. When in doubt, those + these rules are
authoritative.

## Quality bar (non-negotiable)

- **Reusability first**: shared behaviour goes in `packages/*`, never copy-pasted into apps.
- **Strict TypeScript**: no `any`, no unchecked casts; model data with real types.
- **Accessible, performant UI**: WCAG 2.2 AA is a hard requirement — AA colour contrast,
  full keyboard operability and visible focus (see `accessibility.mdc`). RSC by default,
  caching/ISR, semantic HTML.
- **This is a real business**, not a prototype — hold code to production standards.

## Design source of truth

- `docs/design-reference/` is an OLD WordPress/HTML prototype = **loose inspiration only, NOT
  authoritative**. Never copy its tokens, markup or structure.
- The real design system is `docs/design-system.md` + `packages/ui`.

## Definition of Done

`pnpm type-check` and `pnpm lint` pass · no hard-coded colours/spacing · env vars documented
in `.env.example` · shared logic placed in the correct package · Linear ticket updated.
